EfficientDV.filtering_blacklist_file.description: Database of known positions with systematic errors

EfficientDV.exome_intervals.description: A bed file with exome intervals

EfficientDV.dbg_min_base_quality.description: Minimal base quality for local assembly of haplotypes

EfficientDV.hard_qual_filter.description: Any variant with QUAL < hard_qual_filter will be discarded from the VCF file

EfficientDV.num_shards.description: Maximal number of intervals the genome is broken into when parallelizing the make_examples step

EfficientDV.show_bg_fields.description: Show background statistics BG_AD, BG_SB in the output VCF (relevant for somatic calling)

EfficientDV.ref_dbsnp.description: DbSNP vcf for the annotation of known variants

EfficientDV.target_intervals.description: Limit calling to these regions. If target_intervals and intervals_string are not provided then entire genome is used.

EfficientDV.min_variant_quality_snps.description: Minimal snp variant quality in order to be labeled as PASS

EfficientDV.log_make_examples_progress.description: Cause make_examples to output detailed progress information (for debugging)

EfficientDV.optimal_coverages.description: Each sample is downsampled to the "optimal coverage" (dictated by the coverage of the training set). Downsampling method is determined by cap_at_optimal_coverage.

EfficientDV.cap_at_optimal_coverage.description: Defines downsampling behavior. When false, then the reads are downsampled such that the average coverage equals "optimal coverage". When true, each position is downsampled to "optimal coverage".

EfficientDV.base_file_name.description: Prefix for name of all output files

EfficientDV.make_gvcf.description: Whether to generate a gvcf. Default: False

EfficientDV.min_base_quality.description: Minimal base quality for candidate generation

EfficientDV.min_read_count_snps.description: Minimal number of reads, that support a snp, required to  generate a candidate variant

EfficientDV.model_serialized.description: TensorRT model for calling variants, serialized for a specific platform (it is regenerated if not provided)

EfficientDV.call_variants_uncompr_buf_si.description: Memory buffer allocated for each uncompression thread in calll_variants

EfficientDV.min_fraction_hmer_indels.description: Minimal fraction of reads, that support an h-mer indel, required to generate a candidate variant

EfficientDV.min_read_count_non_hmer_inde.description: Minimal number of reads, that support a non-h-mer indel, required to generate a candidate variant

EfficientDV.annotate_systematic_errors.description: Should systematic errors be annotated from a database of common systematic errors

EfficientDV.background_cram_files.description: Background (normal sample) cram files for somatic calling

EfficientDV.p_error.description: Basecalling error for reference confidence model in gvcf

EfficientDV.min_fraction_non_hmer_indels.description: Minimal fraction of reads, that support a non-h-mer indel, required to generate a candidate variant

EfficientDV.min_variant_quality_exome_hm.description: Minimal non-h-mer indel quality in order to be labeled as PASS

EfficientDV.max_reads_per_partition.description: Maximal number of reads that are stored in memory when analyzing an active region

EfficientDV.min_variant_quality_non_hmer.description: Minimal non-h-mer indel quality in order to be labeled as PASS

EfficientDV.intervals_string.description: Regions for variant calling, in the format chrom:start-end. Multiple regions are separated by semi-colon. hese regions. Takes precedence over target_intervals. If both are not provided then entire genome is used.

EfficientDV.allele_frequency_ratio.description: Minimal ratio between the allele frequency in tumor and normal, for vcf filtering

EfficientDV.ug_make_examples_cpus_overri.description: CPU number override for make_examples step

EfficientDV.min_variant_quality_hmer_ind.description: Minimal h-mer indel quality in order to be labeled as PASS

EfficientDV.pileup_min_mapping_quality.description: Minimal mapping quality to be included in image (the input to the CNN)

EfficientDV.references.description: Reference files: fasta, dict and fai, recommended value set in the template

EfficientDV.annotation_intervals.description: List of bed files for VCF annotation

EfficientDV.candidate_min_mapping_qualit.description: Minimal mapping quality for candidate generation

EfficientDV.cram_files.description: Input cram files. Multiple files are merged.

EfficientDV.background_cram_index_files.description: Background (normal sample) cram index files for somatic calling

EfficientDV.model_onnx.description: TensorRT model for calling variants (onnx format)

EfficientDV.output_realignment.description: Output haplotypes and re-aligned reads to a bam file. Default: false.

EfficientDV.prioritize_alt_supporting_re.description: Generate an image with all available alt-supporting reads, and only then add non-supporting reads

EfficientDV.min_read_count_hmer_indels.description: Minimal number of reads, that support an h-mer indel, required to generate a candidate variant

EfficientDV.call_variants_threads.description: Number of decompression threads for call_variants

EfficientDV.scatter_intervals_break.description: The length of the intervals for parallelization are multiples of scatter_intervals_break. This is also the maximal length of the intervals.

EfficientDV.input_flow_order.description: Flow order. If not provided, it will be extracted from the CRAM header

EfficientDV.min_fraction_snps.description: Minimal fraction of reads, that support a snp, required to  generate a candidate variant
